ist, and further analyze the correlation between the samples and diseases. Moreover, the user can build the gene &amp; hotspot list for the specific diseases.With the built-in gene &amp; hotspot list, it may locate the loci related to specific diseases.Users may build the gene list for specific disease as necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Multi-sample comparison<br /></strong>Based on different scenarios (Trio, Case-control, Family-based analysis, etc.), it may set the comparison layers for different samples, so as to easily search key variation position.</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Report generation<br /></strong>Based on different analysis procedure and screening results provided by the system, automatic report generation and downloading can be done.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707526347211502101,707531024515102135,0,'T','Service Workflow','','','','',0,'',0,0),(5,2,707526347211502101,707531024515102135,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526347211502101/sequencing_workflow.png\" alt=\" \" />','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707526347211502101,707531024515102135,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526347320646010/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526347211502101/Genome6.png\" alt=\" \" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526347757402673/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526347211502101/Transcriptome5.png\" alt=\" \" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526350231272401/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526347211502101/Epi5.png\" alt=\" \" /></a><br />&nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526350302550331/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526347211502101/Meta5.png\" alt=\" \" /></a>&nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526350427710537/\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526347211502101/Consulting6.png\" alt=\" \" /></a>&nbsp;</div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707527662240510114,707527663276744466,0,'H','','Sage Link provides complete cloud service to assist our customers in comparing the genetic message between the individuals and clusters. The major functions include file and sample information management, data analysis, computation of allele frequency distribution between the populations, comparison of the difference of variation position between the samples, comparison between the variation position and the known database and the impact prediction of gene function.<br /><br />We display these functions in a convenient user interface that is provided in a clear classification format, thus allowing you to manage various data and analysis results easily. In addition, the big data technology can facilitate the enhancement of operation performance. Users can get their desired information quickly and easily when browsing the genome data or making large-scale computations and analysis.<br /><br />Sage Link&nbsp;assists you in researching the correlation of inherited variation between populations with SOP procedures and high-end technology, which is also dedicated to maintaining the security and privacy of your information.','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526301451264063,707527662611455766,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526301451264063/AboutYourgene_up_1804272.png\" alt=\" \" /><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526301451264063/AboutYourgene_down_180427.png\" alt=\" \" />','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707527454037177231,707527717703702223,0,'T','For NIPT workflow','','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707527454037177231,707527717703702223,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454037177231/NIPT_檢測流程說明_NIPT1.png\" alt=\" \" /><br />\n<ul>\n<li>&nbsp;<span class=\"font_bold\">Step 1</span>：Call +62 21-5723495 (Yourgene Jakart) or email (info@yourgene.com.tw)&nbsp;to ask for more information about NIPT genetic testing.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>&nbsp;<span class=\"font_bold\">Step 2</span>: &nbsp;Sample collection 10ml of blood.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>&nbsp;<span class=\"font_bold\">Step 3</span>: &nbsp;After DNA extraction and completed library preparation, we then process the sample to NGS sequencing and data analysis.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;<span class=\"font_bold\">Step 4</span>: &nbsp;We will provide an individual sample report for each patient.&nbsp;</li>\n<li>&nbsp;<span class=\"font_bold\">Step 5</span>: &nbsp;You can talk to your physician.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(21,1,707303372233275007,707303372530372505,0,'H','','<p><strong><a title=\"Comparative genome analysis of Spiroplasma melliferum IPMB4A, a honeybee-associated bacterium.\" href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23324436\" target=\"_blank\">Comparative genome analysis of Spiroplasma melliferum IPMB4A, a honeybee-associated bacterium.</a></strong></p>\n<p>Wen-Sui Lo, Ling-Ling Chen,&nbsp;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Wan-Chia Chung</span></strong>, Gail E Gasparich, Chih-Horng Kuo</p>\n<p>Jornal：BMC Genomics (2013)</p>\n<p>BACKGROUND:</p>\n<p>The genus Spiroplasma contains a group of helical, motile, and wall-less bacteria in the class Mollicutes. Similar to other members of this class, such as the animal-pathogenic Mycoplasma and the plant-pathogenic \'Candidatus Phytoplasma\', all characterized Spiroplasma species were found to be associated with eukaryotic hosts. While most of the Spiroplasma species appeared to be harmless commensals of insects, a small number of species have evolved pathogenicity toward various arthropods and plants. In this study, we isolated a novel strain of honeybee-associated S. melliferum and investigated its genetic composition and evolutionary history by whole-genome shotgun sequencing and comparative analysis with other Mollicutes genomes.</p>\n<p>RESULTS:</p>\n<p>The whole-genome shotgun sequencing of S. melliferum IPMB4A produced a draft assembly that was ~1.1 Mb in size and covered ~80% of the chromosome. Similar to other Spiroplasma genomes that have been studied to date, we found that this genome contains abundant repetitive sequences that originated from plectrovirus insertions. These phage fragments represented a major obstacle in obtaining a complete genome sequence of Spiroplasma with the current sequencing technology. Comparative analysis of S. melliferum IPMB4A with other Spiroplasma genomes revealed that these phages may have facilitated extensive genome rearrangements in these bacteria and contributed to horizontal gene transfers that led to species-specific adaptation to different eukaryotic hosts. In addition, comparison of gene content with other Mollicutes suggested that the common ancestor of the SEM (Spiroplasma, Entomoplasma, and Mycoplasma) clade may have had a relatively large genome and flexible metabolic capacity; the extremely reduced genomes of present day Mycoplasma and \'Candidatus Phytoplasma\' species are likely to be the result of independent gene losses in these lineages.</p>\n<p>CONCLUSIONS:</p>\n<p>The findings in this study highlighted the significance of phage insertions and horizontal gene transfer in the evolution of bacterial genomes and acquisition of pathogenicity. Furthermore, the inclusion of Spiroplasma in comparative analysis has improved our understanding of genome evolution in Mollicutes. Future improvements in the taxon sampling of available genome sequences in this group are required to provide further insights into the evolution of these important pathogens of humans, animals, and plants.</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526350427710537,707726136426565377,0,'H','','Fill out this form and we will get in touch with you about your project. We are in the Taiwan timezone and typically respond very fast during our business hours. The more details you provide, the faster we can help you.','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707526350427710537,707726136426565377,0,'H','','<iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/a/iifun.com.tw/forms/d/1IOcOaCM4ZQiNLE4MriwbOmJp92_dgKWJq1hVotqT7Vo/viewform?embedded=true\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" width=\"100%\" height=\"800\">載入中&hellip;</iframe>','','','',0,'',0,0),(20,1,707303372233275007,707303372530372505,0,'H','','<p><strong><a title=\"Complete Genome Sequence of Serratia marcescens WW4.\" href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23558532\" target=\"_blank\">Complete Genome Sequence of Serratia marcescens WW4.</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Wan-Chia Chung</span></strong>, Ling-Ling Chen, Wen-Sui Lo, Pei-An Kuo, Jenn Tu, Chih-Horng Kuo</p>\n<p>Jornal：Genome Announc. (2013)</p>\n<p>Serratia marcescens WW4 is a biofilm-forming bacterium isolated from paper machine aggregates. Under conditions of phosphate limitation, this bacterium exhibits intergeneric inhibition of Pseudomonas aeruginosa. Here, the complete genome sequence of S.&nbsp;marcescens WW4, which consists of one circular chromosome (5,241,455 bp) and one plasmid (pSmWW4; 3,248 bp), was determined.</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,1,655407610057157150,707527662761672220,0,'H','','<p>DNAFolder提供完整的雲端服務來協助我們的客戶進行個體及群體間的遺傳訊息比較。主要功能包含檔案及樣品資訊管理，檢視分析資料，計算群體間等位基因的頻率分佈，樣品間變異點位的差異比較，變異點位與已知資料庫的比較以及對基因功能影響的預測。</p>\n<p>我們將這些功能以便捷的使用界面及清晰的分類來呈現，您可以輕易地管理各種資料和分析結果。另外藉由巨量資料的技術來提升運作效能，不管您在瀏覽基因體資料或是進行分析等大型工作量的計算，您都可以快速地得到您有興趣的資訊。</p>\n<p>DNAFolder以標準的工作流程以高端的技術來協助您研究群體間遺傳變異的相關性並且致力維護於您的資訊的安全及隱密性</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,1,655407610057157150,707527662761672220,0,'P','','','','','DNAFolder.png',0,'',0,0),(3,1,655407610057157150,707527662761672220,0,'H','','<ul>\n<li><strong>使用者帳戶管理</strong><strong> (Account access control)<br /></strong>使用者可以申請帳號，透過帳戶管理可以在任何時間、地點直接透過雲端存取、分析樣品資料，並可以依照帳戶權限分享資料。</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>定序資料管理</strong><strong> (Sequence data management)<br /></strong>使用者可以上傳格式為bam/vcf的樣品産生列表，並可將樣品分類管理。此外可使用VEP對樣品變異點位産生註解，以利於進一步篩選分析重要點位。</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>內建與客製化基因及點位列表</strong><strong> (Custom gene &amp; hotspot list)