',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707526353566352314,707532641133432142,0,'C','Applications','<ul style=\"list-style-type:square;\"><li>For the specific diseases with large amounts of clinical test samples and regions of interest, this sequencing method can help the clinical physicians to find and verify the candidate gene or position related to the diseases. It has great application potential in terms of clinical diagnosis and drug development.<li>Various disease researches and clinical applications </li>','','','',0,'L',0,0),(1,2,707526353600304242,707532641201432504,0,'H','','The circulating cell free DNA (cfDNA) is in circulating status out of the cell and without cell status. It widely exists in the serum or plasma of animals, plants and humans. Many previous literatures verify that cancer gene variation is detected in the serum and plasma of the tumor patients, which is consistent with the primary tumor [1.2.3]. That is why cfDNA is valued gradually. Now the researches on circulating DNA promote the development of non-invasive tests. Besides tumor gene screening and monitoring, some other applications are developed, such as prenatal screening. All these can be performed with NGS technologies, which are all non-invasive with low risk and high accuracy.\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526353600304242/tumor_cell_free.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526353600304242/Cell-free_fetal_DNA_2015_11_450.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n<div class=\"tr\">Nature Medicine 20, 548&ndash;554 (2014)；J Clin Oncol. 6, 579-86&nbsp;(2014)</div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707526353600304242,707532641201432504,0,'H','','<p>Refernces: &nbsp;<br />[1]DiazLA, BardelliA. Liquid Biopsies:Genotyping Circulating Tumor DNA[J]. J Clin Oncol, 2014, 32(6):579-586.<br />[2]MarzeseDM, HiroseH, HoonDS. Diagnostic and prognostic value of circulating tumor-related DNA in cancer patients[J]. Expert Rev Mol Diagn, 2013, 13(8):827-844.<br />[3]IgnatiadisM, DawsonSJ. Circulating tumor cells and circulating tumor DNA for precision medicine:dream or reality？[J]. Ann Oncol, 2014, 25(12):2304-2313.<br />[4]AaronMN, ScottVB et al.&nbsp;An ultrasensitive method for quantitating circulating tumor DNA with broad patient coverage.&nbsp;Nature Medicine 20, 548&ndash;554 (2014).</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526350024361037,707531026642023305,0,'H','','Small RNA refers to small RNA molecules with a length of 20~30 nucleotide acids, which mainly regulates the post-translational modification. After bonding with the binding target site on the gene to be regulated, the small RNA makes pyrolysis of the gene transcriptome or directly affects it to translate into protein. In this way, it further achieves the post transcriptional gene silencing reaction, which is also known as RNAi (RNA interference. Small RNA can be roughly classified into siRNA, miRNA and piRNA. siRNA is mostly triggered by the external double-stranded RNA molecules. piRNA is found on the gonad of mammals, and piRNA amplification can be conducted through ping pong cycle. miRNA is produced by the organism and small virus internally, which is found to be involved in various biological regulations, including development, signal transduction, apoptosis, cell division and tumor formation. Studies verify miRNAs can regulate the cell division and apoptosis, promote or suppress the angiogenesis. It also plays a critical role in the formation and evolvement of cancer, thus representing a new cancer promoter and suppressor gene.<br /><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526350024361037/smRNA1.png\" alt=\" \" /><br />\n<p>Small RNA can regulate the gene expression, so it plays a critical role in molecular biology researches. When observing the gene expression in the laboratory, it can apply small RNA in gene knockdown, so scientists can observe the phenotype when the expression of some important genes is reduced. Moreover, small RNA can also be also applied in the battle again plant virus widely and effectively. Before infection, it can inject the virus sequence that can form the double-stranded RNA structure in advance to stimulate RNAi reaction. In the initial phase of virus infection, it can knock down the gene duplicates or transcriptome. With a similar principle, scientists can further apply such technology in gene therapy. Despite being in the development phase, it has great potential in again resisting various major human diseases.</p>\n<p>In traditional researches, miRNA can use microarray to provide miRNAs expression. However, the microarray has a lot of limitations, including hybridization and cross-hybridization factors, fluorescent dye detection problem and design limitations. Moreover, it can&rsquo;t detect the miRNAs that is newly found or has not been found by the previous experiments.</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,2,707526350302550331,707531025372700451,0,'T','Sample Required','','','','',0,'',0,0),(7,2,707526350302550331,707531025372700451,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526350302550331/樣品需求_Whole_genome_Metagenomics3.png\" alt=\" \" />','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707526350302550331,707531025372700451,0,'T','Bioinformatics Solution','','','','',0,'',0,0),(9,2,707526350302550331,707531025372700451,0,'H','','<table style=\"border: 3px solid #ffa500; width: 100%;\" border=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><colgroup><col width=\"89\" /><col width=\"119\" /><col width=\"171\" /><col width=\"104\" /><col width=\"484\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"oa1\" width=\"89\" height=\"38\">\n<div class=\"tc\">Sample type</div>\n</td>\n<td class=\"oa1\" colspan=\"2\" width=\"290\">\n<div class=\"tc\">Application</div>\n</td>\n<td class=\"oa1\" style=\"width: 230px;\">\n<div class=\"tc\">Bioinformatics analysis</div>\n</td>\n<td class=\"oa1\" width=\"484\">\n<div class=\"tc\">Service Solution</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\"oa3\" style=\"width: 230px; height: 239px;\" rowspan=\"12\">\n<div class=\"tc\">DNA