the most common chromosome anomaly that occurs among newborn babies, with an occurrence rate of 1/600-1/1000. The patients show symptoms of low intelligence level at birth, slow physical development, and are often deformed.</p>\n<p><span class=\"font_bold\">Edwards syndrome (Trisomy 18)</span><br />The occurrence rate is about 1/3000. It may cause congenital heart disease, and may deform the appearance and many organs severely. 40% survive up to 1 month, 5% survive up to 1 year old, and 1% survive up to 10 years old.</p>\n<p><span class=\"font_bold\">Patau syndrome (Trisomy 13)</span><br />The occurrence rate is about 1/5000, which is the most serious trisomy among the newborn babies. Over 95% of the babies with such chromosome anomaly die in the uterus. More than half of the patients have holoprosencephaly, which is often accompanied with congenital heart disease. Most patients die within 4~6 months after birth.</p>\n<div class=\"tr\">(Data Source: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell-free_fetal_DNA\" target=\"_blank\">Wikipedia</a>)</div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,2,707526337417435230,707742114534502676,0,'H','','<hr />','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707526337417435230,707742114534502676,0,'H','','<hr />','','','',0,'',0,0),(5,2,707526337417435230,707742114534502676,0,'C','Alan Chang, Esq. | General Counsel','Mr Chang holds the responsibility for legal policies, corporate governance, intellectual property and commercial licensing in Yourgene.                                                               \n\nPrior to joining Yourgene Bioscience, Mr Chang served as inhouse legal counsel at Powerchip Technology Corporation and then senior legal affairs manager at ScinoPharm Taiwan. At Innolux Corp (an affiliate of Foxconn Technology Group), Mr Chang served as General Counsel and is involved in numerous legal and business negotiations on behalf of Innolux. \n\nMr Chang received his J.D., cum laude, from the University of Melbourne Law school and Masters in IP Management from University of London.','','','Alan4_376564_BK5.png',0,'L',0,0),(1,2,707526345775276435,711052772017757665,0,'H','','Yourgene bioinformatic staffs are available to help with basic NGS data analysis and consulting. We also &nbsp;provide advanced and customized NGS data analysis, database integration, and best Bioinformatics solutions for researchers or clinicians.','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707527454754603641,707727717433515517,0,'H','','<div class=\"tl\">\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 85px;\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><span class=\"font_bold font_18px\">Step 1</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454754603641/How12.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td>Call +886 2 2675 8068 to ask for more information about genetic testing. Please consult us or talk to your physician.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\">&nbsp;<span class=\"font_bold font_18px\">Step 2</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454754603641/How3.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td>You or your doctor will receive a collection&nbsp;tube (buccal swab)and an&nbsp;informed consent form that should be signed by the patient.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><span class=\"font_18px font_bold\">&nbsp;Step 3</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454754603641/How2.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;The buccal swab should be labeled with the individual&rsquo;s name and date of birth. Use the swab to wipe both sides of cheek around 20~30 times. Place it till dry and prevent contamination.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><span class=\"font_18px font_bold\">&nbsp;Step 4</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454754603641/How4.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Fill up the informed consent form and&nbsp;confirm&nbsp;the buccal swab labeled with the individual&rsquo;s name and date of birth. Sent to <a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526337647402102/\" target=\"_blank\">Yourgene Jakart</a>.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><span class=\"font_18px font_bold\">&nbsp;Step 5</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454754603641/How5.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Yourgene Bioscience will receive&nbsp;your sample and processes your DNA by NGS and bioinformatics analysis.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><span class=\"font_18px font_bold\">&nbsp;Step 6</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454754603641/How6.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Yourgene Bioscience&nbsp;delivers the test results in approximately 30-40 days.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div class=\"tc\"><span class=\"font_24px\"><a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454037177231/\" target=\"_blank\">Genetic Testing Servieces Workflow</a></span></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(5,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'H','','<p>Inherited diseases&nbsp;Genetic testing can evaluate people with recessive, inherited diseases like sickle cell anemia, Tay-Sachs disease, or cystic fibrosis.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Anyone, especially those with a history of genetic disease in the family.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'T','What are the requirements for performing the test?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(7,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'H','','<p>BRCA1/2 Genetic Testing&nbsp;from Yourgene Core Lab is performed using buccal cells by oral swab: a way to collect DNA from the cells on the inside of a person\'s cheek. &nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454754603641/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW IT WORK</a></p>\n<p>Report delivery time: approximately 30 days. &nbsp;<a title=\"How to get the Test step by step\" href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454037177231/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW TO GET THE TEST</a></p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'T','Service Workflow','','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'T','Who should get the genetic testing for breast cancer, ovarian cancer and prostate cancer detection?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'H','','<p>BRCA1/2 Genetic Testing&nbsp;&nbsp;screens BRCA1 and BRCA2 genes&nbsp;via high&shy; throughput massive sequencing (also known as&nbsp;next generation sequencing&nbsp;or NGS) related&nbsp;breast cancer, ovarian cancer and prostate cancer.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This test&nbsp;evaluates the risk of breast cancer, ovarian cancer and prostate cancer&nbsp;based on the internationla database.</li>\n<li>Annotation database including, PolyPhen2 , SIFT, dbSNP, COSMIC, ClinVar and OMIM.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454405671447/BRCA12_3.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454405671447/Wallions16215.png\" alt=\" \" /><br />\n<p>Approximately 5% to 10% of&nbsp;breast cancer&nbsp;is hereditary, caused by abnormal genes passed from parent to child. The risk of a woman developing&nbsp;ovarian or breast cancer&nbsp;is greatly increased if she inherits a harmful mutation in the&nbsp;BRCA1 or BRCA2 genes. Men with these mutations also have a&nbsp;higher risk of prostate cancer, and both men and women may be at greater risk of developing other types of cancer.</p>\n<p>The&nbsp;BRCA1/BRCA2 gene test&nbsp;from&nbsp;Yourgene Bioscience allows both genes to be analyzed in order to localize<strong>&nbsp;</strong>mutations in BRCA1 and BRCA2&nbsp;in people with a&nbsp;family history&nbsp;suggesting the possible presence of a harmful mutation in one of these genes.</p>\n<p>Performing the test allows, in the case of a positive result, appropriate follow-up measures to be adopted, and/or early and&nbsp;personalized&nbsp;breast cancer detection&nbsp;both for the patient and their relatives.</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707527454405671447,707532651004257211,0,'T','What is BRCA1/2 Genetic Testing ?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(7,1,655406000146410734,655407617763250660,0,'T','市面上各家NIPT與NIPT +服務，有勁具有哪些優勢？','','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,1,655406000146410734,655407617763250660,0,'H','','<div class=\"tl\"><span class=\"font_18px\">有勁基因體核心實驗室除了有ISO9001認證，還擁有由三位博士帶領的生物資訊團隊及專業醫療顧問來把關檢測結果，將錯誤率降到最低，提升檢測品質達到高規格的服務，讓每位孕婦都可獲得最完善的報告。在報告當中，除了<span class=\"font_underline\">唐氏症、愛德華氏症及巴陶氏症染色體</span> (NIPT)及<span class=\"font_underline\">微小染色體片段缺失</span> (NIPT +)風險程度評估外，有勁亦能於NIPT與NIPT+報告中另呈現：<br /><br /></span></div>\n<span class=\"font_18px font_bold\" style=\"color: #800000;\">(一)其他對染色體風險程度評估</span>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/1/Messagess00_Pics655406000146410734/NIPT_其他染色體風險評估.png\" alt=\" \" width=\"1054\" height=\"568\" /></div>\n<p><span class=\"font_18px font_bold\">報告結果區分三種：低度風險、中度風險與高度風險。</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span class=\"font_18px\">低度風險，則胎兒染色體異常的機會很低，一般不會再進行羊膜穿刺或絨毛膜採樣檢查。</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"font_18px\">中度風險，代表的是檢測結果數值落在低度風險與高度風險之間，為求慎重，建議重新採血並再進行一次NIPT非侵入性產前染色體篩檢，重新進行的篩檢費用由有勁負擔。</span></li>\n<li><span class=\"font_18px\">高度風險，則建議進行傳統的侵入性檢查（羊膜穿刺或絨毛膜採樣檢查），以進一步確認胎兒是否異常。</span></li>\n</ul>\n<span class=\"font_18px font_bold\" style=\"color: #800000;\">(二) 胎兒DNA比列</span>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/1/Messagess00_Pics655406000146410734/NIPT_檢體DNA資訊_胎兒DNA比例.png\" alt=\" \" width=\"731\" height=\"420\" /></div>\n<div class=\"tl\"><span class=\"font_18px\">為何胎兒DNA含量如此重要？胎兒DNA含量可做為「非侵性產前染色體檢測」的品質控制之一。一般來說孕婦血液中含有胎兒DNA，這項檢測是針對胎兒DNA得知風險程度，但若在孕婦血液中胎兒DNA含量過低，將造成偽陽性/偽陰性導致結果誤判，因此<span class=\"font_bold\" style=\"color: #ff0000;\">有勁在2016年初開始提供胎兒DNA含量 &nbsp;(Fetal DNA fraction)來嚴格把關這項檢測的準確性。</span></span></div>\n<div class=\"tc\"><br /><img src=\"/UpFiles/1/Messagess00_Pics655406000146410734/NIPT_胎兒DNA含量_流程圖.png\" alt=\" \" width=\"952\" height=\"368\" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,1,655406000146410734,655407617763250660,0,'C','只需“採集孕婦血液”就可得知胎兒染色體套數是否異常？','<p>由於母體孕育胎兒期間，必須透過胎盤與血液循環，進行營養提供與廢物代謝以維持胎兒的成長發育。因此，透過孕婦周邊靜脈血液獲取游離的胎兒DNA片段 (Cell-free fetal DNA ，cffDNA)，分析胎兒的染色體結構，進而確認胎兒是否患有唐氏症、愛德華氏症及巴陶氏症等染色體異常疾病。 (圖片來源：網路)</p>','','','Cell-free_fetal_DNA_2015_11_450.png',0,'R',0,0),(2,2,707526337417435230,707742114534502676,0,'H','','<hr />','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707526337417435230,707742114534502676,0,'C','Keng Hsu, CPA | Chief Operating Officer','Mr. Hsu serves as CFO of Yourgene Bioscience, with responsibility for finance, tax and investor relations. In addition, he is also responsible for business development for markets outside Taiwan. He travels frequently to offer Yourgene\'s expertise in NIPT solution and genetic test services to clients.\n\nBefore joining Yourgene Bioscience, Keng served as a Financial Analyst with Ford and later GE Captial as an Associate. He also started 3 separate successful businesses in property development, online business and share investments.\n\nMr. Hsu is a certified public accountant and holds a Master Degree in Property Finance and a Bachelor Degree in Commerce at University of Melbourne, Australia.','','','keng_Hsu_376.png',0,'L',0,0),(7,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'T','Service Workflow','','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454336375705/套組內容_猝死2_eng.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'T','What is Sudden Cardiac Death Genetic Testing ?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'H','','<p>Sudden Cardiac Death Genetic Testing screens 328 genes&nbsp;via high&shy; throughput massive sequencing (also known as&nbsp;next generation sequencing&nbsp;or NGS) related sudden cardiac death&nbsp;diseases.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This test&nbsp;evaluates the risk of sudden cardiac death&nbsp;diseases&nbsp;based on the internationla database.</li>\n<li>Annotation database including, PolyPhen2 , SIFT, dbSNP, COSMIC, ClinVar and OMIM.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'T','Who should get the genetic testing for sudden cardiac death diseases detection?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'H','','<p>Sudden Cardiac Death Genetic Testing&nbsp;can evaluate people with pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH) and sudden Cardiac arrest (SCA).&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Anyone, especially those with a history of genetic disease in the family.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(5,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'T','What are the requirements for performing the test?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,2,707527454336375705,707532651352632311,0,'H','','<p>The Inherited Disease Genetic Testing&nbsp;from Yourgene Core Lab is performed using buccal cells by oral swab: a way to collect DNA from the cells on the inside of a person\'s cheek. &nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454754603641/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW IT WORK</a></p>\n<p>Report delivery time: approximately 30 days. &nbsp;<a title=\"How to get the Test step by step\" href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454037177231/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW TO GET THE TEST</a></p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'T','Service Workflow','','','','',0,'',0,0),(9,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454316646307/套組內容_心血管3_eng.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'T','What are the requirements for performing the test?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(7,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'H','','<p>Cardiomyopathy Genetic Testing&nbsp;from Yourgene Core Lab is performed using buccal cells by oral swab: a way to collect DNA from the cells on the inside of a person\'s cheek. &nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454754603641/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW IT WORK</a></p>\n<p>Report delivery time: approximately 30 days. &nbsp;<a title=\"How to get the Test step by step\" href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454037177231/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW TO GET THE TEST</a></p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454316646307/sunset-hands-love-woman.png\" alt=\" \" /><br /><br />According to the 10 major death causes released by the Health Promotion Administration, Ministry of Health and Welfare in recent years, heart disease and cardiomyopathy disease have always topped the list. The high fatality rate of cardiomyopathy disease is because most cardiomyopathy diseases have no warning signal in advance. Once cardiomyopathy disease causes stroke or myocardial infarction, it will lead to fatal or irreversible consequences, which will bring burden to the whole family. Although cardiomyopathy disease is closely correlated to aging, it doesn&rsquo;t mean it will never occur to young people. Now many young people are stressed and very busy with work, they might ignore the fact that stress is one of the factors that may increase the possibility of cardiomyopathy disease.','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'T','What is Cardiomyopathy Genetic Testing ?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'H','','<p>This&nbsp;genetic test&nbsp;screens 62 genes&nbsp;via high&shy; throughput massive sequencing (also known as&nbsp;next generation sequencing&nbsp;or NGS) related cardiomyopathy&nbsp;diseases.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This test&nbsp;evaluates the risk of cardiomyopathy&nbsp;diseases&nbsp;based on the internationla database.</li>\n<li>Annotation database including, PolyPhen2 , SIFT, dbSNP, COSMIC, ClinVar and OMIM.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454316646307/cardio_631.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'T','Who should get the genetic testing for cardiomyopathy diseases detection?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(5,2,707527454316646307,707532651542300024,0,'H','','<p>Cardiomyopathy Genetic Testing&nbsp;can evaluate people with cardiomyopathy&nbsp;diseases&nbsp;like dilated cardiomyopathy (DCM), hypertrophic cardiomyopathy (HCM), left ventricular noncompaction cardiomyopathy (LVNC) and long QT syndrome (LQTS).&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Anyone, especially those with a history of genetic disease in the family.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(11,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'H','','<ol>\n<li>Douglas Hanahan, Robert A. Weinberg. <strong>The hallmarks of cancer.</strong><em>Cell.</em>2000; <strong>100</strong>: 57&ndash;70</li>\n<li>Douglas Hanahan, Robert A. Weinberg. <strong>Hallmarks of Cancer: The Next Generation.</strong><em>Cell.</em>2011; <strong>114</strong>(5): 646-74</li>\n</ol>','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,1,655406000214612474,655407624275323424,0,'T','全方位心血管疾病基因檢測 - 規格說明','','','','',0,'',0,0),(10,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'T','Reference','','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'T','Service Workflow','','','','',0,'',0,0),(9,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454261416433/套組內容_癌症2_eng.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(6,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'T','What are the requirements for performing the test?','','','','',0,'',0,0),(7,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'H','','<p>The Inherited Disease Genetic Testing&nbsp;from Yourgene Core Lab is performed using buccal cells by oral swab: a way to collect DNA from the cells on the inside of a person\'s cheek. &nbsp;<a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454754603641/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW IT WORK</a></p>\n<p>Report delivery time: approximately 30 days. &nbsp;<a title=\"How to get the Test step by step\" href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707527454037177231/\" target=\"_blank\">HOW TO GET THE TEST</a></p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'H','','<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707527454261416433/baby-caucasian-child-daughter-53590.png\" alt=\" \" /><br /><span class=\"font_bold\"><br />Cancer&nbsp;</span>is the leading cause of death all the time in&nbsp;worldwide. The cancer occurrence is mainly due to various gene mutations in the cell. After a lot of gene mutations are accumulated, it may finally lead to cancer [1, 2 ].&nbsp;Our&nbsp;Cancer Genetic Testing&nbsp;aims to help people and families with a history of cancer better understand and manage their cancer risk.','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707527454261416433,707532651757476272,0,'H','','<p>This&nbsp;genetic test&nbsp;screens 50 genes&nbsp;via high&shy; throughput massive sequencing (also known as&nbsp;next generation sequencing&nbsp;or NGS) related various cancer.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>This test&nbsp;evaluates the risk of cancer based on the internationla database.</li>\n<li>Annotation database including,&nbsp;PolyPhen2 , SIFT, dbSNP, COSMIC, ClinVar and OMIM.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526341114115136,707533745155534033,0,'H','','<table border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<h3>Illumina HiSeq 2500</h3>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 400px;\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341114115136/Illumina_2500_2_2015_11_500322_去背.png\" alt=\" \" /></td>\n<td>\n<p>The Illumina HiSeq 2500 platform is a rapid, high-throughput, next-generation sequencing platform that runs on two modes: &nbsp;</p>\n<p><span class=\"font_bold\">Rapid-Run Mode</span><br />The rapid run mode provides quick results, allows efficient processing of a limited number of samples, and offers support of longer paired-end 150 bp reads. It provides up to 1.2 billion paired-end reads or 180 Gb of data per run, which enable greater depth of coverage and improved assembly for de novo applications.</p>\n<p><span class=\"font_bold\">High-Output Mode</span><br />The high output mode is perfect for larger studies with more samples or when the greatest depth of coverage is required. High output mode allows you to batch process approximately five times more samples than rapid mode and provides up to 6 billion paired-end reads with 600 Gb of data per run.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707526341114115136,707533745155534033,0,'H','','<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"30\" align=\"left\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 500px;\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341114115136/IonProton_2015_11_500322.png\" alt=\" \" /></td>\n<td style=\"width: 500px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341114115136/IonPGM_2015_11_500322.png\" alt=\" \" /></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 500px;\">\n<h3>Ion Proton&nbsp;</h3>\nThe sequencing system of Life Technologies is known as the 2.5-Generation sequencer. It is mainly because the sequencing method applies the semi-conductor component for detection. The NGS system applies the optical system for sequencing the images. Therefore, the sequencing is faster than other generations of sequencing systems. Yourgene&rsquo;s Ion Proton sequencing platform is suitable for providing various target sequencing panel services, such as cancer panel, inheritance disease panel, etc.&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 500px;\">\n<h3>Ion PGM</h3>\nThe Ion Torrent PGM&trade; System combines semiconductor sequencing technology with natural biochemistry to directly translate chemical information into digital data. The system leverages the exponential improvements in the semiconductor industry (known as Moore&rsquo;s Law) to provide scalability and flexibility for various applications. The system&rsquo;s use of the simplest, natural sequencing chemistry eliminates the need for expensive optics and reduces complex chemistries to measure natural DNA extension.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707526345570117331,707533750520774406,0,'H','','<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526345570117331/TAF_2738.png\" alt=\" \" /></td>\n<td style=\"width: 400px;\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526345570117331/Illumina_CSPro_1_2015_11_s.png\" alt=\" \" /><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526345570117331/ion_torrent_EXOME_認證_s.png\" alt=\" \" /></td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 400px;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526341141136766,707533746327146014,0,'C','Ion Chef (Front-end Processing System of Automated Sequencing Chip)',' <span>','','','Ion_Chef_500322.png',0,'L',0,0),(2,2,707526341141136766,707533746327146014,0,'C','Optical Mapping(Whole Genome Mapping Assembly System)',' <span>','','','banner-opgen_500322.png',0,'L',0,0),(3,2,707526341141136766,707533746327146014,0,'C','Perkin Elmer Automated NGS Library System（NGS Express）','<span>','','','69673-4881861_500322.png',0,'L',0,0),(4,2,707526341141136766,707533746327146014,0,'H','','<br />\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"15\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"303\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341141136766/lsr_experion_station_300267.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"306\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341141136766/Qubit_3002671.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"303\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341141136766/NanoDrop_3002671.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"303\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><strong><strong>Experion Fully-automated CE System</strong><br /></strong></div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"306\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><strong>Qubit 2.0 Super Micro Fluorometer&nbsp;</strong></div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"303\">\n<div class=\"tc\"><strong>NanoDrop 2000 Super Micro Optical Luminance Meter</strong></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>','','','',0,'',0,0),(30,2,707526350467746234,707527463440255470,0,'H','','<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"http://journals.plos.org/plosone/article?id=10.1371/journal.pone.0068518\">The Complete Plastid Genome Sequence of Madagascar Periwinkle Catharanthus roseus (L.) G. Don: Plastid Genome Evolution, Molecular Marker Identification, and Phylogenetic Implications in Asterids&nbsp;</a></strong></p>\n<p>Chuan Ku,&nbsp;<strong>Wan-Chia Chung</strong>, Ling-Ling Chen, Chih-Horng Kuo</p>\n<p>Jornal：PLoS One (2013)</p>\n<p>The Madagascar periwinkle (<em>Catharanthusroseus</em>&nbsp;in the family&nbsp;<em>Apocynaceae</em>) is an important medicinal plant and is the source of several widely marketed chemotherapeutic drugs. It is also commonly grown for its ornamental values and, due to ease of infection and distinctiveness of symptoms, is often used as the host for studies on phytoplasmas, an important group of uncultivated plant pathogens. To gain insights into the characteristics of apocynaceous plastid genomes (plastomes), we used a reference-assisted approach to assemble the complete plastome of&nbsp;<em>C. roseus</em>, which could be applied to other&nbsp;<em>C. roseus</em>-related studies. The&nbsp;<em>C. roseus</em>&nbsp;plastome is the second completely sequenced plastome in the asterid order&nbsp;<em>Gentianales</em>. We performed comparative analyses with two other representative sequences in the same order, including the complete plastome of&nbsp;<em>Coffeaarabica</em>&nbsp;(from the basal&nbsp;<em>Gentianales</em>&nbsp;family&nbsp;<em>Rubiaceae</em>) and the nearly complete plastome of&nbsp;<em>Asclepiassyriaca</em>&nbsp;(<em>Apocynaceae</em>). The results demonstrated considerable variations in gene content and plastome organization within&nbsp;<em>Apocynaceae</em>, including the presence/absence of three essential genes (i.e.,&nbsp;<em>accD</em>,&nbsp;<em>clpP</em>, and&nbsp;<em>ycf1</em>) and large size changes in non-coding regions (e.g.,&nbsp;<em>rps2</em>-<em>rpoC2</em>&nbsp;and IRb-<em>ndhF</em>). To find plastome markers of potential utility for&nbsp;<em>Catharanthus</em>&nbsp;breeding and phylogenetic analyses, we identified 41&nbsp;<em>C. roseus</em>-specific simple sequence repeats. Furthermore, five intergenic regions with high divergence between&nbsp;<em>C. roseus</em>&nbsp;and three other euasterids I taxa were identified as candidate markers. To resolve the euasterids I interordinal relationships, 82 plastome genes were used for phylogenetic inference. With the addition of representatives from&nbsp;<em>Apocynaceae</em>&nbsp;and sampling of most other asterid orders, a sister relationship between&nbsp;<em>Gentianales</em>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em>Solanales</em>&nbsp;is supported.</p>','','','',0,'',0,0),(4,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'T','The advantages of Yourgene Core Lab:','','','','',0,'',0,0),(5,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<ul>\n<li>ISO 17025 accreditation and&nbsp;TAF certified.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.illumina.com/services/service-partners-and-programs/cspro.html\" target=\"_blank\">Illumina Certified Service Provider</a> (CSPro)</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.thermofisher.com/tw/zt/home/life-science/sequencing/next-generation-sequencing/certified-service-providers-program.html\" target=\"_blank\">Ion Torrent&trade; Certified Service Provider Program</a></li>\n<li>All experiments performed according to Standard Operating Procedures.</li>\n<li>Samples handled by continuously trained technicians.</li>\n<li>Instrument calibration periodically.</li>\n<li>Traceable sample storage.</li>\n<li>Quality sample reporting.</li>\n<li>Extensive customer support.</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526347211502101,707531024515102135,0,'H','','Next Generation Sequencing (NGS) technology is widely applied in basic scientific research, from microbiology, agriculture to human genomic research. Yourgene NGS services provide the newest and different kind of platforms, e.g. Illumina HiSeq2500, Ion Proton&trade; System, The Ion Torrent PGM&trade; System and Ion S5&trade;. And we are experienced in all sequencing applications, including genome sequencing, transcriptome sequencing, epigenome sequencing and metagenome sequencing. We also provide NGS consulting; <a href=\"/en/content/messagess/contents/707526350427710537/\" target=\"_blank\">Request a quote</a> for professional and high quality NGS services.','','','',0,'',0,0),(14,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'T','Traceable sample storage','','','','',0,'',0,0),(15,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/樣品倉儲管理_2.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/樣品倉儲管理.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/樣品倉儲管理_3.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\nThe samples are classified and stored in an appropriate environment. With strict warehousing system, the samples from several years ago can also be looked up in a short time. Moreover, the concentration information is inputted in the database for easy retrieval. The laboratory performs 24-hour temperature monitoring for all refrigerators, so as to guarantee the samples and agents are kept under good condition.','','','',0,'',0,0),(12,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'T','QC for Sequencing','','','','',0,'',0,0),(13,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/step4_3002.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/Proton_Chip_2015_11_3002.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/Step4NGS定序品管_S5_300150.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\nAfter the above QC procedures, NGS sequencing of the samples can be finally done. The sequencing is still conducted with a rigorous attitude.<br />\n<ul>\n<li>SOP of ISO17025 standards are followed to guarantee stable quality.</li>\n<li>Complete experimental records are kept for each key step, including the concentration information when operating on the machine.</li>\n<li>A strict temperature and humidity control mechanism is applied for the machine environment.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>','','','',0,'',0,0),(8,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'T','QC for Library Preparation','','','','',0,'',0,0),(9,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/a.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/b.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/c.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n<ol>\n<li>For the samples passing QC, a library will be created based on the customer&rsquo;s requirements.</li>\n<li>In conformation to the SOP of ISO17025 standards, it guarantees stable library quality.</li>\n<li>It keeps complete experimental records for each key step, including the Gel Electrophoresis Diagram, which can be provided for customer query.</li>\n<li>Each sample tube is labeled in different colors, so as to avoid wrong transfer.</li>\n<li>Samples handled by continuously trained technicians,&nbsp;maintain the optimal quality of the experiment.&nbsp;</li>\n</ol>','','','',0,'',0,0),(10,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'T','Library Validation','','','','',0,'',0,0),(11,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/4.Qubit測量__.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/5._自動電泳__.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/6._QPCR測量__.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n<ol>\n<li><span class=\"font_bold\">Qubit Measurement:</span><br />It can precisely measure the library concentration using the fluorescence quantitative method.</li>\n<li><span class=\"font_bold\">Automated Electrophoresis:</span><br />It confirms the library length (bp) and concentration through highly-sensitive automated electrophoresis.</li>\n<li><span class=\"font_bold\">QPCR Measurement:</span><br />To increase the accuracy of concentration measurement, it tests the concentration through precise QPCR, so as to achieve the optimal sequencing quality.</li>\n</ol>','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'T','Quality Assurance','','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<span class=\"font_bold\">Sequencing quality is the most important for a leading service provider in genomics. Yourgene Core Lab is ISO 17025 accredited and TAF certified. We&nbsp;provide customers with stable and reliable sequencing data.</span>','','','',0,'',0,0),(1,2,707526345633557505,707533747760155362,0,'P','','','','','高階軟硬體設備_(2).png',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707526345633557505,707533747760155362,0,'H','','Currently Yourgene set up an independent machine room with high specifications. All computing devices are equipped with 284-core and 5T memory, including the host with a memory reaching 3TB. Moreover, it is equipped with 250T high-capacity network storage system to store the giant sequencing data and the analysis data after genome sequencing. With UPS on all computer devices in the machine room, data integrity is guaranteed.','','','',0,'',0,0),(7,2,707526341021643664,707533747534127306,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/1.收件確認_1_.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/2._Nanodrop測量__.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341021643664/3._Qubit測量__.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>\n<ol>\n<li><span class=\"font_bold\">Checking of the received samples:</span><br />Once samples are received, the trained technicians&nbsp;will carefully check each tube to confirm whether the sample name is consistent with that written on the shipment sheet, and whether it is damaged or overflowed during its transportation. If everything is fine, the samples will be labeled with a unique code, and stored in an appropriate environment for follow-up confirmation of sample quality.</li>\n<li><span class=\"font_bold\">Nanodrop measurement:</span><br />The purity of the nucleic acids is measured in this step, and the sample is checked as to whether it was contaminated by impurities such as protein.</li>\n<li><span class=\"font_bold\">Qubit measurement:</span><br />It can precisely measure the DNA or RNA amount using the fluorescence quantitative method.</li>\n</ol>','','','',0,'',0,0),(3,2,707526341054745607,707533750152513005,0,'T','Yourgene Jakart Laboratory Team','','','','',0,'',0,0),(2,2,707526341054745607,707533750152513005,0,'H','','<div class=\"tc\"><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341054745607/實驗室團隊_up_1000602.png\" alt=\" \" />&nbsp;<br /><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341054745607/實驗室團隊_1_2015_11_333.png\" alt=\" \" /><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341054745607/實驗室團隊_3_2015_11_333.png\" alt=\" \" /><img src=\"/UpFiles/2/Messagess00_Pics707526341054745607/實驗室團隊_2_2015_11_333.png\" alt=\" \" /></div>','','','',0,'',0,0),(11,2,707526347320646010,707532640567635300,0,'H','','<table class=\"overview\" style=\"border: 3px solid #ffd700; width: 100%;\" border=\"3\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"83\">\n<div class=\"tc\" align=\"center\">Sample type</div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"105\">\n<div class=\"tc\" align=\"center\">Application</div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"91\">\n<div class=\"tc\" align=\"center\">Bioinformatics analysis</div>\n</td>\n<td width=\"711\">\n<div class=\"tc\" align=\"center\">Service Solution</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 230px;\" rowspan=\"7\">\n<div class=\